    AbstractParser
    The AbstractParser class is an abstract implementation of the Parser interface that provides a skeletal implementation of the parse and addToIndex methods.

    The DictionaryParser class extends AbstractParser and is responsible for parsing the dictionary file and adding the words and their definitions to the index.

    The EBookParser class extends AbstractParser and is responsible for parsing the ebook file and adding the words and their page locations to the index.
    IndexOutputter
    The IndexOutputter class is responsible for writing the index to a file.

    The MenuFunctions class provides the logic for processing user input and executing the appropriate action.
    Parser
    The Parser interface defines methods for parsing a file and adding words to an index.

    StopWordsParser
    The StopWordsParser class extends AbstractParser and is responsible for parsing the stop words file and adding the words to the stop words set.
    WordDetail
    The WordDetail class represents a word and its associated details such as its definition, page numbers, and word count.
